properties.peddleDesc: A Succor Ring will allow you to come back to a place you have previously visited!
An Identify Ring will allow you to identify items and see their hidden properties!

properties.desc: You enter the tavern to the shouts of "Hey Stranger!" from a man named Darwin behind the counter.
You sneak through a wall and into the guild of thieves. Who knew they were so crafty?
You find yourself in a room magically projecting the elements of nature.
You enter a small dojo jam-packed with weapons and armor.
You find yourself in a small room that smells like incense.
You find yourself in a small bank, clearly well-traveled. A sign nearby says "NO SOLICITORS."
You find yourself in the commerce center of Rylt. Weapons, armor, and various utilities can be found here.
You step on a faceplate that says "Last Chance" as if it's taunting you into continuing further.
You find yourself in the town smithy. The temperature is overwhelming.
You slowly open the door to the gaze of a crazed man standing on a tanned bear. He offers to tan your hides.
You enter a small building, lined to the brim with bottles and potions of varying sorts. Your nostrils burn with the mixture of pungent scents.
You walk through a secret wall and see blood everywhere. Uh oh...
You walk past the entrance and feel a strong magical vibration. The leaders of the pack are here.
You find yourself near a cave. You see magical constructs walking around and their puppeteers not far away.
You find yourself in a spooky clearing.
You feel an overwhelming sense of dread, the renegade commander must be nearby.
You find yourself in the central renegade camp.
You see one of the renegade leaders, brandishing his weapon.
You see one of the renegade leaders, brandishing his weapon.
You step over the scarecrow, and see a hidden hole in the ground.
As brutish as they are, you suspect some of the renegades have been hiding out here, reading books.
You find yourself near a dilapidated building. It seems to have one occupant, somehow, despite it's state.
You find yourself in a strange place beneath the renegade cornfield. There is one person here in the corner, reading books.
You are standing near a hole in the ground. You see the puddle dripping water down below. You could probably climb down safely.
You see a shrine here. What it is worshipping, nobody knows, but it can't be good.
You see what once was a thriving slack-off area for prison guards.
As you enter the room, you see a shimmering floor tile opposite you.
You have a sense of dread as you near the door.
You find yourself in a submerged cave area.
You step into a manmade bog. The stench is overwhelming.
You find yourself in a strange place beneath the renegade cornfield. There is one person here in the corner, reading books.
You find yourself in a submerged cave area.
You find yourself in a submerged cave area.
You step through the door and see rings and gems of all manners strewn about the small office-apartment.
You step inside the Last Chance - a prison for those who oppose the natural order of things. The hairs on your neck stand up at the thought of going downstairs.
You enter the cozy cabin in the woods. You see a mayoral figure glancing in your direction as you enter.
As you slink through the wall, you see more blood on the floor. You wonder how dangerous it could possibly be here.
You find yourself in a non-descript building on the outskirts of town.
You find yourself in a small outpost. One guard is stationed inside.
You find yourself in a festive portal area, with all manner of holiday connections.
